  </Placemark>
  <Placemark>
    <name>The Lively</name>
    <description><![CDATA[Surfside City Hall. Bronze plaque on pink granite boulder.<br/><br/><b>Address:</b> 1304 Monument Drive, Surfside Beach<br/><br/><b>Marker Text:</b> The Lively, first vessel with emigrants to Austin's colony landed here December 23, 1821. The Battle of Velasco was fought here June 26, 1832. Public and secret treaties of peace between the Republic of Texas and General Santa Anna were signed here May 14, 1836. Dedicated May 14, 1936.]]></description>
    <Point><coordinates>-95.299723,28.942867,0</coordinates></Point>
  </Placemark>
